{"schema_version":"1","crate":"langkit_support","version":"26.0.0","id":"dbd09099ed57e344","name":"AdaSAT","qualified_name":"AdaSAT","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":12,"column":9},"code":"package AdaSAT","documentation":{"description":"The root package of the AdaSAT library. Defines the base data structures\nthat are used everywhere else.\nYou should instantiate the `AdaSAT.DPLL` package with your own theory or\nuse the `AdaSAT.Helpers.DPLL_Solve` function to start solving!"},"simple_types":[{"id":"9fd361c01b1d4df0","name":"Literal","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Literal","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":27,"column":9},"code":"type Literal is private;","documentation":{"description":"A positive or negative occurrence of a variable"}},{"id":"88431bd629d8f7b8","name":"Variable","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Variable","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":13,"column":9},"code":"type Variable is new Positive;","documentation":{"description":"A boolean variable, which can appear positively or negatively in a\nliteral. For example, ``-2`` represents ``¬2``. From literals, we can\nbuild clauses, and then formulas. Ultimately, the solver's job is to\nassign the value ``True`` or ``False`` to each variable so that the\ngiven formula is satisfied. The set of assignments is called a model.\n\nNote that we represent variables as positive integers so that we can\ndirectly use them as keys in arrays (for example in the ``Model`` type),\nrather than, say strings (which would require replacing arrays by\nhash maps) or records (which would require extra indirections)."}},{"id":"7dca44280be62133","name":"Variable_Value","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Variable_Value","kind":"ada_simple_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":53,"column":9},"code":"type Variable_Value is (True, False, Unset);","documentation":{"description":"A variable can either be set to True or False, or Unset","enumeration_literals":[{"name":"True","description":""},{"name":"False","description":""},{"name":"Unset","description":""}]}}],"array_types":[{"id":"7bd6ee4dc6561730","name":"Literal_Array","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Literal_Array","kind":"ada_array_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":42,"column":9},"code":"type Literal_Array is array (Positive range <>) of Literal;","documentation":{"description":"Note that we don't use a generalized access type to avoid users from\ngiving stack-allocated clauses to the solver."}},{"id":"0e652f2d4ab6d9df","name":"Model","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Model","kind":"ada_array_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":56,"column":9},"code":"type Model is array (Variable range <>) of Variable_Value;","documentation":{"description":"A mapping from variable to its value"}}],"access_types":[{"id":"742d1eb06fdba801","name":"Literal_Array_Access","qualified_name":"AdaSAT.Literal_Array_Access","kind":"ada_access_type","location":{"file":"../../../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/adasat_26.0.0_37336738/6f3afbf6370f902fe56119609f32f0517b74fea1f3171527704eb834a6db7450/src/adasat.ads","line":43,"column":9},